    <body>
      <section eId="sec_1052">
        <num>1052</num>
        <heading>Prohibiting the use of employment promissory notes and other similar provisions</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_1052__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>requires the worker to repay to the employer any sums advanced to\nsuch worker by the employer, unless such sums were used to pay for\ntraining related to the worker's employment with the employer;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1052__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>requires the worker to pay the employer for any property it has\nsold or leased to such worker;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1052__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>requires educational personnel to comply with any terms or\nconditions of sabbatical leaves granted by their employers; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_1052__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>is entered into as part of a program agreed to by the employer and\nits workers' collective bargaining representative.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
